template_id: openagreements-restrictive-covenant-ohio
name: Employee Restrictive Covenant (Ohio)
category: non-compete
description: >-
  Ohio-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement built for Ohio's
  common-law reasonableness regime: there is no general Ohio non-compete
  statute, so every post-employment restraint stands or falls on the three-part
  Raimonde v. Van Vlerah test (no greater than required to protect the employer,
  no undue hardship on the employee, not injurious to the public). It provides
  confidentiality and trade-secret protection backstopped by the Ohio Uniform
  Trade Secrets Act (R.C. 1333.61-1333.69), a continued-at-will-employment
  consideration recital (Lake Land Emp. Group of Akron, LLC v. Columber),
  customer and employee non-solicitation, an optional non-compete tied to
  identified protectable interests and sized to the actual footprint, a
  litigation-extension tolling clause (Homan, Inc. v. A1 AG Servs., L.L.C.),
  express assignment beyond a statutory merger (Acordia of Ohio, L.L.C. v.
  Fishel), physician public-interest scrutiny (MetroHealth Sys. v. Khandelwal;
  Williams v. Hobbs), and discretionary judicial reformation that the drafting
  does not rely on (Raimonde empowers modification; Kross Acquisition Co. v.
  Groundworks Ohio, LLC makes it discretionary; Cintas Corp. v. Perry prices
  overreach). Drafted as a starting point for licensed counsel review.
