      Conservative default. The non-compete is the most heavily scrutinized
      covenant under Ohio's reasonableness framework; a customer non-solicit
      backstopped by the Ohio Uniform Trade Secrets Act often protects the
      employer as well. Include only after confirming an identified protectable
      interest (confidential information, trade secrets, or customer goodwill)
      and sizing the duration and territory to the actual footprint.
