    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Ohio imposes no statutory cap on duration; courts weigh time and territory
      together against the employer's real protectable interest under Raimonde, so there
      is no safe-harbor number. 12 months matches the modal non-compete term observed in
      benchmarked, publicly-filed employee agreements — a conservative default counsel
